Quick start

From the project root:
cd backend
npm install
cp .env.example .env and edit .env values as needed
node server.js
API base: http://localhost:5000/api
Notes

Upload location: by default the backend writes runtime upload files to the OS temp folder (safe for local development). Do NOT set UPLOAD_DIR to a path inside the project workspace if you want to avoid Live Server/editor auto-reloads.
To override uploads location set UPLOAD_DIR to an absolute path outside the repo, e.g. C:\temp\cnssid_uploads.
Sharp on Windows

If npm install fails on sharp, try:
npm rebuild sharp --update-binary
If problems persist, install Visual Studio Build Tools or use WSL/Docker; then reinstall.
Sharp on Windows

If npm install fails on sharp, try:
npm rebuild sharp --update-binary
If problems persist, install Visual Studio Build Tools or use WSL/Docker; then reinstall.
Troubleshooting

Ensure your .env values are correct (DB connection, JWT secret).

If frontend shows "Could not connect to server", confirm backend running and port matches .env.
Optional: override upload dir (absolute path outside project)
UPLOAD_DIR=C:\temp\cnssid_uploads